---
title: VIMC Research Lead at Imperial College London – closing date 12 January 2020
---

We are [recruiting a Research Lead](https://www.imperial.ac.uk/jobs/description/MED01576/research-fellow-or-advanced-research-fellow) for the Vaccine Impact Modelling Consortium, based within the consortium secretariat at Imperial College London. This is a collaborative project, and would be a great opportunity for an established researcher to drive our research agenda, working closely with the consortium’s modelling/research groups, Gavi, BMGF and other major global health bodies (notably the World Health Organization) and with public health policy-makers in low and middle-income countries. 

Closing date: 12 January 2020
